text.tspan: An Improved Clustering Topic Model with Density
Peak Detection and Lexical-Semantic Term Importance
Clustering transformer embeddings is the most popular
Top2Vec and BERTopic use UMAP and HDBSCAN,
which in theory allows them to discover the number of clusters...
...but as we will see, in practice they grossly overestimate it..
a) Top2Vec estimates term importance based on distance from
centroids, but clusters are based on density, and are not spherical.
b) BERTopic generates junk topics filled with stop words.
I estimate term importance scores based both on lexical and
semantic valence by using a combination of word embedding
proximity to weighted average embedding and NPMI.
I introduce the Peax clustering algorithm, which finds peaks in a
kernel density estimate, then estimates components as a
mixture of Multivariate Gaussians. (also UMAP TSNE)
I evaluate Topeax, BERTopic and Top2Vec on MTEB(eng, v2) clustering tasks + BBC, and Tweets. Topic quality (Cin, Cex, diversity, interpretability)
and cluster quality (FMI) are monitored. I ran robustness checks to subsampling and hyperparameters.
